{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Duocylinder",
  "description": "Duocylinder — 4D torus (Cartesian product of two circles) drawn as a grid of u-/v-neighbor lines, rotating continuously through the XY, ZW, and XW planes. Atom-decomposed in tranche 5 of the 2nd-pass audit: the bundled `node.generate_duocylinder_vertices` is gone — the (u, v)-parametric surface is now a pure graph composition over the new parametric-surface atom family.\n\nThe inner graph reads as TouchDesigner Pattern-CHOP shape:\n  `generate_grid_uv(24) → (u_values, v_values)` flattens (iu, iv) ∈ [0,24)² to two 576-entry Array<f32> sweeps over [0, TAU).\n  `array_math(Cos|Sin)` per axis → cos_u / sin_u / cos_v / sin_v.\n  `array_math(ScaleOffset, scale=0.176776695)` per channel applies the 4D magnitude normalisation (= 0.25/sqrt(2) — keeps the rendered duocylinder visually identical to the legacy generator since every duocylinder point pre-bake has 4D magnitude sqrt(2), so this normalises to a 0.25 sphere matching the legacy PROJ_SCALE screen-fit factor).\n  `pack_vec4(x, y, z, w) → Array<Vec4Vertex>` zips the four scaled channels into the typed 4D vertex wire.\n  `edges_from_grid_uv(24) → Array<EdgePair>` emits the u-wrap + v-wrap topology (1152 edges).\n\nThe spine is unchanged: three `node.math` nodes turn `time × rate` into per-plane angles fed into `node.rotate_4d`; `node.project_4d` performs the two-stage 4D→3D→2D perspective collapse; `node.render_lines` carries the line + dot rendering.\n\nThe same atom family (`generate_grid_uv` + `array_math` + `pack_vec4` + `edges_from_grid_uv`) authors any (u, v)-parametric surface — torus, Klein bottle, geodesic sphere, terrain mesh — without a new Rust primitive per shape.\n\nLegacy outer-card param names (`xy` / `zw` / `xw` / `verts` / `v_size` / `anim`) are aliased to the new general-user names for save-file backward compatibility.",
